Package: ggdocumentation
Title: Adds documentation to 'ggplot2' plots using grid objects
Description: Allows users to document their 'ggplot2' plots following Edward Tufte's 
    Principles of Analytical Design Principle 5: Documentation (from Tufte's book 
    "Beautiful Evidence") by adding company logo (sponsor), author name, date 
    produced, and data source. Also supports integrating 'ggthemes'.
URL: https://github.com/joshuaadampoirier/ggdocumentation
License: GPL (>= 2)
Version: 1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Joshua", "Poirier", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "josh.poirier@gmail.com"))
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.2)
Imports:
    grid (>= 3.3.2),
    ggplot2 (>= 2.2.1),
    png (>= 0.1.7)
Suggests:
    ggthemes (>= 3.4.1),
    testthat
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Collate:
    'ggdocumentation.R'
    'doc_plot.R'
    'themes.R'
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
